en


I looked down at the table in front of me. A white porcelain plate and teacup were surrounded by roughly a drawer's worth of silverware.

en


I remembered my late wife lovingly instructing me on the particulars of Rumburgian high tea etiquette.

en


The outermost spoon was for spreading jam on scones. The middle spoon was exclusively for stirring tea, while the inner spoon was for eating petits fours.

en


Before I left, Pabel had lovingly instructed me on the particulars of Rumburgian high tea etiquette.

en


No matter how many times I had high tea in Rumburg, I still didn't have a clue which spoon to use for what.

She gestured for me to sit down, then took her own seat across from me.

"No longer rising on the Queen's arrival? You really have changed, Your Majesty."

en


"So splendid to see you, Your Majesty."

With an imperious frown, she took a seat across from me.

She smiled and took a seat across from me.

A look of annoyance crossed Queen Beatrice's face.

en


"So, Your Majesty. I suppose you know why I've asked you to join me here."

en


"To give me a belated wedding gift for Vina?"

en


"To apologize for sanctioning us at the AN?"

en


"Please enlighten me."

en


"I can hazard a guess."

en


"Sorry, Bea, but Intermerkopum applications are closed at this time."

LineNo: 16314609,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't make me laugh.
en


"Don't make me laugh."

LineNo: 16314711,

Beatrice Livingston (R): As if I'd want any part in that.
en


"As if I'd want any part in that."

LineNo: 16315091,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Rizia has embarrassed itself on a...
en


"Rizia has embarrassed itself on a global scale, Your Majesty. The entire Alliance of Nations agrees."

LineNo: 16315193,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And rubbed salt in our wounds with...
en


"And rubbed salt in our wounds with the formation of your silly little regional alliance."

LineNo: 16315851,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You are allowing populist sentimen...
en


"You are allowing populist sentiment to dictate the direction of your kingdom. What's next? You'll hand over the throne?"

LineNo: 16316231,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Your formerly prodigious resources...
en


"Your formerly prodigious resources are dwindling, meaning that your usefulness to Rumburg is as well."

LineNo: 16316611,

Beatrice Livingston (R): The reports I'm hearing of widespr...
en


"The reports I'm hearing of widespread riots... most unbefitting of a once-great kingdom such as yours."

LineNo: 16316713,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And furthermore--
en


"And furthermore--"

en


Our server returned with a silver tray of piping hot scones and a crystal ramekin of rose-hip jam.

en


"You remember your tea etiquette. Very good."

en


"But that is not enough to mend the rift between us, Your Majesty."

en


"The rift between us is too deep to be mended, Your Majesty."

en


"And I fear you have neither the mettle nor the stomach for what's coming."

en


"What is coming, Your Excellency?"

LineNo: 16318163,

Player_Romus: Let me guess. You're planning some...
en


"Let me guess. You're planning something involving Sordland."

Beatrice Livingston (R): You have turned your back on your...
en


"You have turned your back on your most loyal of trade partners...."

LineNo: 16318923,

Beatrice Livingston (R): With the formation of your silly l...
en


"With the formation of your silly little regional alliance, you have turned your back on your most loyal of trade partners."

LineNo: 16319025,

Player_Romus: I have more mettle than you ever w...
en


"I have more mettle than you ever will, Beatrice."

LineNo: 16319127,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Oh, you'll find out soon enough.
en


"Oh, you'll find out soon enough."

LineNo: 16319229,

Beatrice Livingston (R): If I were, I would *never* tell a...
en


"If I were, I would *never* tell a Sord-lover like you."

LineNo: 16319609,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't go around making ridiculous...
en


"Don't go around making ridiculous accusations, Romus."

LineNo: 16319711,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You wouldn't last a minute on the...
en


"You wouldn't last a minute on the Rumburgian throne."

LineNo: 16320091,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You wouldn't last a minute on the...
en


"You wouldn't last a minute on the Rumburgian throne. Lena told me that herself."

LineNo: 16320193,

Narrator: She drew herself upright and stared...
en


She drew herself upright and stared coldly at me.

LineNo: 16320295,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I have spoken to the others. Your...
en


"I have spoken to the others. Your GRACE membership has been rescinded. Effective immediately."

LineNo: 16320525,

Player_Romus: Rizia has outgrown the need for GR...
en


"Rizia has outgrown the need for GRACE anyway."

LineNo: 16320897,

Player_Romus: The age of monarchies is over. All...
en


"The age of monarchies is over. All of you will fall sooner or later."

LineNo: 16320999,

Player_Romus: I harbor no ill feelings towards y...
en


"I harbor no ill feelings towards your decision. You will always be family to me."

LineNo: 16321101,

Player_Romus: A natural development. Geopolitica...
en


"A natural development. Geopolitical relationships evolve over time, after all."

LineNo: 16321473,

Player_Romus: I hope you don't see Intermerkopum...
en


"I hope you don't see Intermerkopum as a threat. We can still work together in some capacity."

LineNo: 16321575,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You'll never win your war without...
en


"You'll never win your war without us. That much is certain."

LineNo: 16321955,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Forget about it. You have made you...
en


"Forget about it. You have made your priorities clear."

LineNo: 16322335,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You are not my family, Your Majest...
en


"You are not my family, Your Majesty. My niece is. And you drove her away."

LineNo: 16322715,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You are not my family, Your Majest...
en


"You are not my family, Your Majesty. My niece is. And you've left her to rot in Pales."

LineNo: 16323095,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You are not my family, Your Majest...
en


"You are not my family, Your Majesty. My niece is. And you and that Azaro harlot are conspiring to steal her birthright."

LineNo: 16323197,

Beatrice Livingston (R): If I happen to see you while visit...
en


"If I happen to see you while visiting Vina, I will be cordial. That's all I can promise."

LineNo: 16323299,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You'll never hold your own against...
en


"You'll never hold your own against the superpowers without us. That much is certain."

LineNo: 16323401,

Narrator: Our server cleared the uneaten scon...
en


Our server cleared the uneaten scones from the table. Two of his colleagues delicately put down a towering etagere spilling over with petit fours.

en

en

en


She stood up and left in a huff.

Beatrice Livingston (R): Now you make a mockery of our tea...
en


"Now you make a mockery of our tea culture. I've had enough, King Romus."

Beatrice Livingston (R): Well. I'm glad we can at least enj...
en


"Well. I'm glad we can at least enjoy our tea like civilized people."

en


"You were just guessing, weren't you?"

LineNo: 16325287,

Player_Romus: So have I.
en


"So have I."

LineNo: 16325389,

Player_Romus: Why should it matter what spoon I...
en


"Why should it matter what spoon I use? They all look the same."

Player_Romus: It was nice knowing you, Queen Bea...
en


"It was nice knowing you, Queen Beatrice."

LineNo: 16325593,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Hrmph.
en


"Hrmph."

Narrator: We stood up and shook hands. As her...
en


We stood up and shook hands. As her attendants escorted me out of the room, I took one look back at the almost-full cup of tea on the table.

Narrator: I never liked it anyway.
en


I never liked it anyway.

"I know full well which spoons to use, thank you."

en

"I was just guessing. I don't actually care which spoon I use."

en


"Civilized compared to whom?"

As her attendants escorted me out of the room, I took one look back at the almost-full cup of tea on the table.

en


"Ha. I confess I'll miss your visits."

en


"I will give you one guess."

LineNo: 16326715,

Beatrice Livingston (R): So how is that war of yours going?
en


"So how is that war of yours going?"

LineNo: 16327119,

Player_Romus: Great. Swimmingly. We're on track...
en


"Great. Swimmingly. We're on track to win the whole thing."

LineNo: 16327221,

Player_Romus: You know it's impolite to bring up...
en


"You know it's impolite to bring up such subjects over tea."

LineNo: 16327323,

Player_Romus: God is guiding our troops to a sur...
en


"God is guiding our troops to a surefire victory."

LineNo: 16327695,

Player_Romus: About that... I think we could use...
en


"About that... I think we could use Rumburg's help again."

LineNo: 16327797,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You're not kidding.
en


"You're not kidding."

LineNo: 16327899,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We're family. You can talk to me a...
en


"We're family. You can talk to me about anything."

LineNo: 16328001,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Is that so?
en


"Is that so?"

LineNo: 16328659,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't be so modest.
en


"Don't be so modest."

LineNo: 16328761,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I was ever so excited to learn abo...
en


"I was ever so excited to learn about Rizia's victory in Operation Golden Shield."

LineNo: 16328863,

Beatrice Livingston (R): It was ever so tragic the way you...
en


"It was ever so tragic the way you lost Operation Golden Shield, despite Rumburg doing its best to assist you."

LineNo: 16329243,

Beatrice Livingston (R): But as for Total Tranquility... I...
en


"But as for Total Tranquility... I am worried your military doesn't have what it takes."

LineNo: 16329623,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Now you seem to be stuck in the mi...
en


"Now you seem to be stuck in the mire, with no end in sight."

LineNo: 16329725,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And your military seems to be hold...
en


"And your military seems to be holding its own in the second operation thus far."

LineNo: 16329827,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And our poor Vina is still behind...
en


"And our poor Vina is still behind enemy lines, if she is alive at all..."

LineNo: 16330207,

Beatrice Livingston (R): The Alliance of Nations has turned...
en


"The Alliance of Nations has turned against you..."

LineNo: 16330587,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Your soldiers don't seem to know w...
en


"Your soldiers don't seem to know which end of their guns to point at the enemy."

LineNo: 16330967,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I will grant that you haven't rack...
en


"I will grant that you haven't racked up all that many kills."

LineNo: 16331069,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You are racking up a respectable n...
en


"You are racking up a respectable number of kills."

LineNo: 16331171,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Correct me if I'm wrong, my dear,...
en


"Correct me if I'm wrong, my dear, but it seems Rizia is rather fucked."

en

"Look at you. You don't even know the right way to put jam on a bloody scone."

LineNo: 16331833,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You remembered your tea etiquette....
en


"You remembered your tea etiquette. All is not completely lost."

LineNo: 16332325,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I'll admit I thought our Vina woul...
en


"I'll admit I thought our Vina would be returned home by this point in the conflict."

LineNo: 16332705,

en


"Of course, I wasn't expecting the Alliance of Nations to turn against you..."

LineNo: 16332807,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Overall, the outcome is far from d...
en


"Overall, the outcome is far from decided. But I do trust your kingdom to rip the Palesians a new arsehole."

LineNo: 16333187,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Then again, perhaps my trust was m...
en


"Then again, perhaps my trust was misplaced. You don't even know the right way to put jam on a bloody scone."

LineNo: 16333305,

Player_Romus: Your faith in me is heartening, de...
en


"Your faith in me is heartening, dear sister-in-law. I promise I will win this for Rizia and Rumburg."

LineNo: 16333685,

Beatrice Livingston (R): The fact that you remembered your...
en


"The fact that you remembered your tea etiquette bolsters my confidence even further."

LineNo: 16333803,

Player_Romus: I don't want to beg. But is there...
en


"I don't want to beg. But is there anything you can do for us?"

LineNo: 16333905,

Player_Romus: Please, Beatrice. Can't Rumburg he...
en


"Please, Beatrice. Can't Rumburg help a fellow monarchy out?"

LineNo: 16334007,

Player_Romus: The situation is nowhere near as b...
en


"The situation is nowhere near as bad as you describe. I have everything under control."

LineNo: 16334109,

Player_Romus: It might look like we're doing wel...
en


"It might look like we're doing well, but our troops are suffering out there. Is there anything you can do to help us?"

Player_Romus: I know we're going to win. But a l...
en


"I know we're going to win. But a little extra insurance from Rumburg wouldn't hurt us."

Beatrice Livingston (R): I know you will.
en


"I know you will."

LineNo: 16334415,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I'm afraid another military aid pa...
en


"I'm afraid another military aid package is out of the question."

LineNo: 16334517,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We're going to need everything we'...
en


"We're going to need everything we've got for what's coming."

LineNo: 16334913,

Player_Romus: What is coming, Your Excellency?
en


"What is coming, Your Excellency?"

LineNo: 16335015,

Player_Romus: Let me guess. You're planning some...
en


"Let me guess. You're planning something against Sordland."

LineNo: 16335395,

en


"Oh, you'll find out soon enough."

en


"If I were, I wouldn't tell a Sord-lover like yourself."

en


"Shh. They've got ears everywhere."

LineNo: 16335701,

Player_Romus: I don't like the sound of that.
en


"I don't like the sound of that."

LineNo: 16335803,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't fret. It's nothing I would a...
en


"Don't fret. It's nothing I would ask your kingdom to involve itself in."

LineNo: 16335905,

Beatrice Livingston (R): All is peaceful in Rumburg so far....
en


"All is peaceful in Rumburg so far. But with neighbors like ours, we must be prepared for the worst."

LineNo: 16336007,

Beatrice Livingston (R): What I can offer you, Your Majesty...
en


"What I can offer you, Your Majesty, is a chance for peace."

LineNo: 16336125,

Player_Romus: I don't want peace. I want the Gul...
en


"I don't want peace. I want the Gulf of Ales to run red with blood."

LineNo: 16336227,

Player_Romus: I like the sound of that. Tell me...
en


"I like the sound of that. Tell me more."

LineNo: 16336607,

Player_Romus: I have only ever wanted peace. It...
en


"I have only ever wanted peace. It is the Palesians who are the warmongerers."
